Gene onthology (GO) enrichment analysis

library(tidyverse)
library(clusterProfiler)
library("enrichplot")
library(readr)
#devtools::install_github("YuLab-SMU/enrichplot")

term2name <- read_tsv("term2name_GO.tsv")

#to translate IPR IDs to GO:
IPR_GO <- read.csv("IPR2GO.csv", sep = ",", quote = "", header = T,  stringsAsFactors = FALSE, fill = TRUE)
IPR_GO$IPR <- sub("^[^:]*:([^ ]+).*", "\\1", IPR_GO$IPR)
IPR_GO$GO <- trimws(IPR_GO$GO, which = "left") #delete a space in front of GO:
term2gene<- IPR_GO[, c(2, 1)]

background_genes <- IPR_GO$IPR

Up-regulated genes after 30 days drought vs Control

DEG30vsC<- read_tsv("all-30vsC.tsv", show_col_types = FALSE)
DEG30vsC_UP<-DEG30vsC[DEG30vsC$diffexpressed == "UP", ]

enrichment <- enricher(DEG30vsC_UP$IPR,
                       TERM2GENE = term2gene,
                       TERM2NAME = term2name,
                       pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                       qvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                       universe = background_genes,
                       pAdjustMethod = "fdr",
                       minGSSize = 1,
                       gson = NULL)

result<-enrichment@result
result[result$p.adjust < 0.05, c("Description", "GeneRatio", "RichFactor", "BgRatio", "p.adjust", "qvalue", "Count")]

KEGG enrichment analisis

Up-regulated genes after 30 days drought vs Control

data_KEGG <- read.table("KEGG_annotation.txt", sep = "\t", quote = "", row.names = NULL, stringsAsFactors = FALSE, fill = TRUE)
colnames(data_KEGG)[1] = "NODE"
colnames(data_KEGG)[2] = "KEGG"
length(unique(data_KEGG$KEGG))
## [1] 750
data <- read.table("annotation_data_filtered.tsv", sep = "\t", quote = "", header = T,  stringsAsFactors = FALSE, fill = TRUE)
colnames(data)[1] = "NODE"
colnames(data)[4] = "PF"
colnames(data)[11] = "IPR"

IPR2KEGG <- merge(data, data_KEGG, by = "NODE")
sum(IPR2KEGG$KEGG == "", na.rm = TRUE)
## [1] 7600
term2gene <-na.omit(IPR2KEGG[, c("KEGG","IPR")])
term2name<-na.omit(IPR2KEGG[, c("KEGG", "KEGG")])

background_genes <-term2gene$IPR


enrichment <- enricher(DEG30vsC_UP$IPR,
                       TERM2GENE = term2gene,
                       TERM2NAME = term2name,
                       pvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                       qvalueCutoff = 0.05,
                       universe = background_genes,
                       pAdjustMethod = "fdr",
                       minGSSize = 1,
                       gson = NULL)

result<-enrichment@result
result[result$p.adjust < 0.05, c("Description", "GeneRatio", "RichFactor", "BgRatio", "p.adjust", "qvalue", "Count")]

BUSCOs <- read_delim("BUSCOs.tsv", delim = "\t", escape_double = FALSE, trim_ws = TRUE, show_col_types = FALSE, col_names = T)
## Warning: One or more parsing issues, call `problems()` on your data frame for details,
## e.g.:
##   dat <- vroom(...)
##   problems(dat)
BUSCOs$NODE <- sub(":.*$", "", BUSCOs$Sequence)

IPR2BUSCO <- merge(data, BUSCOs, by = "NODE")
term2gene <-na.omit(IPR2BUSCO[, c("Description","IPR")])
term2name<-na.omit(IPR2BUSCO[, c("Description", "Description")])

background_genes <-term2gene$IPR
